	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97109325111205><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: What to keep in your spell slots?</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=584><span id= >Chriskaballa</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 9th 8:07 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I am a level 11 cleric, and have heard stories from other clerics. You should ALWAYS have the following spells equipped:<br><br>Divine Aura<br>your most recent Symbol<br>Gate<br><br>These 3 spells are infinitely valuable to you.... if you are ever in a tight spot, Symbol yourself (if you aren't already), then Divine Aua to get the hell outta there, then once you put some distance between you and the baddies, Gate home (or, for me and the other wanderers, whatever passes for home. :))<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Chriskaballa<br>11th level cleric<br>The Nameless</td></tr>
