<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=97534885513283></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97534885513283><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=97534885513283>Level 20</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=97534885513283#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2508><span id= >Drusk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 27th 1:14 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree that the spells are situational.<br><br>Personally I only carry 1 heal spell (Healing) as Light Healing bites for all classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I get G. Healing I will carry both Healing and G. Healing.<br><br>I also keep Smite memmed.  I am in Lake of Ill Omen now, so I also have Expulse since there are plenty of Undead.<br><br>I have Root, which I use for the obvious reason of keeping the fleeing goblin around where we can blast and bash it without it grabbing his friends.  I also use Root to get the MOB off of the caster.<br><br>I am playing with Holy Might.  I like the fact that it stuns MOBs.<br><br>I have Spirit Armor and Daring memmed.<br><br>And finally Divine Aura.  Never know when you might need it.<br><br>I don't keep gate memmed (at least not at the Lake).  It hardly ever is a quick escape.  If I need to gate, I usually have time to memming it.  I also can mem Create Food and Water, temporarily getting rid of something else.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
